
                                            The officials are accused of using an id document of a 64-year-old bed ridden man to illegally process roadworthy certificates for hundreds of motorists.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - Four roadworthy testing centre officials will appear at the Tembisa magistrates court on Wednesday morning on charges of fraud. The officials are accused of using an identity document of a 64-year-old bed ridden man to illegally process roadworthy certificates for hundreds of motorists. They were arrested on Monday as part of an operation to arrest corrupt traffic officials this festive season. Road Management Traffic Corporation’s Simon Zwane says: “Allegations that they have been issuing roadworthy certificates to vehicles that they never tested and they were using the ID documents of a man who’s sick and in bed at home.  “Hundreds of these have been issued and they are under investigation .”